Bangladesh beat Sri Lanka by 2 wickets in a tensioned filled T20I at the Khettarama Stadium, Colombo and secured their place in the Nidahas Trophy final against India on Sunday.Chasing 160 to win, the Bangladeshis reached the target off 19.5 overs thanks to a six by Mahmudullah off Isuru Udana.Mahmudullah remained 43 not out off 18 balls.Tamim Iqbal also made 50.Sri Lanka made 159 for 7.